# Xiao Yang is fascinated by our relationship with abandoned houses, factories, castles, sewers, and any kind of dark places shrouded in ghostly silence. These places seem to tell stories and despite their creepy mood, they want to be explored. This experimental photo series called “Love Letter” shows a skillful blend of people and gloomy places. The people seem to be one with these places. Xiao Yang used the effect of multiple exposure to create a deep connection between human being and the respective place. Each image of the photo series conveys a gloomy atmosphere, full of loneliness and surreal beauty.")
